thread.title_full: Offensive player of the week (9/14): Keller's Tyler Tutt | Dallas Morning News

author: Michael Florek
title: Offensive player week (9/14): Keller's Tyler Tutt
text:
Tyler Tutt; Keller
What he did: In matchup between 2-0 teams in Keller and Rowlett, Tutt rushed 26 times for 342 yards and six touchdowns as Keller won, 56-41. Rowlett led 27-21 before Tutt broke off a 69-yard touchdown run just before halftime. He then scored on 34- and 54-yard runs in the third quarter and an eight-yard run in the fourth to give Keller 21 straight points. He also had a 46-yard in the first quarter.
Who is he? A 5-11, 200-pound senior running back.
The stats: Tutt has 69 carries for 686 yards and nine touchdowns this year.
He said it: "I believe my quarterback (told me). He came up to me in the locker room and just showed me his phone. I was like, 'I didn't know I did that.' I just ran over to my o-linemen and gave them a hug."
Coach said it: "It's been, probably back in the '90s when I was in Florida, since I've seen anybody take off with the breakaways that he had. It was really impressive. I was really glad he was on our team." â” Carl Stralow
Did you know? Tutt has pledged to play for Texas State in college. He chose the Bobcats over offers from Iowa, Boise State, and a number of others. ... Tutt is also on Keller's track team. He runs the 100 meters, 200 meters the relays in those events.
